      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:1:17:6",
      "text": [
        " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) عَنِ الْوُضُوءِ لِلصَّلَاةِ فَقَالَ مَرَّةٌ مَرَّةٌ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Al Hassan, and someone else, from sahl Bin Ziyad, from Ibn Mahboub, from Ibn Rabaat, from Yunus Bin Ammar who said, ",
          "‘I asked Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> about the Ablution <span class=\"iTxt\">(Wudhu)</span> for the <span class=\"iTxt\">Salaat</span>, so he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘(Washing the face) once, (washing the hands) once’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Muhammad ibn al-Hassan and others have narrated from Sahl ibn Ziyad from ibn Mahbub from ibn Ribat from Yunus ibn ‘Ammar who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about Wudu’ for Salah (prayer). He (the Imam) said, ‘It is (washing the face) once and (hands) once.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
